usdMplsMIB.name: usdMplsMIB

revisions.description: Fixed SMIv2 conformance. Added RowStatus support to usdMplsIfMinorPathOptionTable, usdMplsTunnelProfilePathOptionTable, usdMplsTunnelProfileDynamicEndpointTable and usdMplsTunnelProfileTunnelEndpointTable.
Initial version of this MIB module.

usdMplsMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@Juniper.net
usdMplsMIB.description: The MultiProtocol Label Switching (MPLS) MIB for the Unisphere Networks enterprise. This MIB contains managed objects for basic MPLS configuration of: 1. Global tasks - common MPLS usage configurations on a given label switching router (LSR). 2. Interface tasks - MPLS interface (major interface) configurations. 3. Tunnel tasks - tunnel interface (minor interface) configurations. 4. Tunnel profile tasks - configured to be used by multiple MPLS tunnels. 5. Explicit paths - supports dynamic and manual configurations of explicit paths. 6. VPNs - supports constraint-based routing label distribution protocol (CR-LDP) and BGP/MPLS virtual private network (VPN) configurations.

UsdMajorCfgVciRanges.name: UsdMajorCfgVciRanges
UsdMajorCfgVciRanges.description: Generic VCI label range specifier for both resource reservation protocol (RSVP) and label distribution protocol (LDP).

UsdMajorCfgVpiRanges.name: UsdMajorCfgVpiRanges
UsdMajorCfgVpiRanges.description: Generic VPI label range specifier for both resource reservation protocol (RSVP) and label distribution protocol (LDP).

UsdMinorCfgBWRanges.name: UsdMinorCfgBWRanges
UsdMinorCfgBWRanges.description: Specifies bandwidth requirements for each MPLS tunnel.

UsdMinorCfgHoldingAndSetupPriorityRanges.name: UsdMinorCfgHoldingAndSetupPriorityRanges
UsdMinorCfgHoldingAndSetupPriorityRanges.description: Each LSP has a setup and hold priority before setting it up or preempting it relative to the other LSPs. This convention specifies those ranges.

UsdMinorCfgRetryTimesAndNorouteRanges.name: UsdMinorCfgRetryTimesAndNorouteRanges
UsdMinorCfgRetryTimesAndNorouteRanges.description: RSVP/LDP will have a number of retries for successfully setting up a tunnel. This value specifies retry value ranges for LDP/RSVP with or without no-route notification.

UsdMinorCfgRetryIntervalAndNorouteRanges.name: UsdMinorCfgRetryIntervalAndNorouteRanges
UsdMinorCfgRetryIntervalAndNorouteRanges.description: RSVP/LDP will have time interval between two successive retries for setting up tunnel successfully. This value specifies the interval ranges for LDP/RSVP with or without no-route notification.

UsdProfileCfgBWRanges.name: UsdProfileCfgBWRanges
UsdProfileCfgBWRanges.description: Bandwidth range specified for each tunnel in tunnel profiling.

UsdProfileCfgHoldingAndSetupPriorityRang.name: UsdProfileCfgHoldingAndSetupPriorityRanges
UsdProfileCfgHoldingAndSetupPriorityRang.description: Tunnel setup and hold priority range specified for each tunnel in tunnel profile configuration.

UsdProfileCfgRetryTimesAndNorouteRanges.name: UsdProfileCfgRetryTimesAndNorouteRanges
UsdProfileCfgRetryTimesAndNorouteRanges.description: Range specified for number of retries for tunnel with or without no-route notification for RSVP/LDP.

UsdProfileCfgRetryIntervalAndNorouteRang.name: UsdProfileCfgRetryIntervalAndNorouteRanges
UsdProfileCfgRetryIntervalAndNorouteRang.description: Range specified for retry interval for tunnel with or without no-route notification for RSVP/LDP.

usdMplsGroupMplsEnable.name: usdMplsGroupMplsEnable
usdMplsGroupMplsEnable.description: Enables or disables MPLS on the virtual router. When MPLS is created on the virtual router (VR), it remains adminstratively disabled untill it is enabled explicitly. Without administratively enabling the MPLS on VR, it won't function as an LSR even though it holds the MPLS configurations until the MPLS context is destroyed for the VR.

usdMplsGroupReopTimer.name: usdMplsGroupReopTimer
usdMplsGroupReopTimer.description: All LSPs setup in MPLS domain are reoptimized for better LSPs as and when available. This object allows configuration of the frequency of reoptimization in time interval.

usdMplsGroupLabelRangeLow.name: usdMplsGroupLabelRangeLow
usdMplsGroupLabelRangeLow.description: The lower end of the range of the platform label space from which the interfaces on a given LSR derive their label space. Ethernet interfaces can use only platform label space while ATM interfaces can use either platform or interface label space. For the successful configuration of the label range both lower and higher end values must be set cuncurrently.

usdMplsGroupLabelRangeHigh.name: usdMplsGroupLabelRangeHigh
usdMplsGroupLabelRangeHigh.description: The higher end of the range of the platform label space from which the interfaces on a given LSR derive their label space. Ethernet interfaces can use only platform label space while ATM interfaces can use either platform or interface label space. For the successful configuration of the label range both lower and higher end values must be set cuncurrently.

usdMplsGroupLspRetryTimesNoroute.name: usdMplsGroupLspRetryTimesNoroute
usdMplsGroupLspRetryTimesNoroute.description: This object configures the number of retries for LSP setup after a failure due to no available route.

usdMplsGroupLspRetryIntervalNoroute.name: usdMplsGroupLspRetryIntervalNoroute
usdMplsGroupLspRetryIntervalNoroute.description: This object configures the time interval between two successive LSP setup retries after a failure due to no available route.

usdMplsGroupLspRetryTimes.name: usdMplsGroupLspRetryTimes
usdMplsGroupLspRetryTimes.description: Use this object to configure number of retries for LSP setup after a failure other than one due to no available route.

usdMplsGroupLspRetryInterval.name: usdMplsGroupLspRetryInterval
usdMplsGroupLspRetryInterval.description: Use this object to configure the time interval between two LSP setup retries after a failure other than one due to no available route.

usdMplsGroupLdpRetryTimesNoroute.name: usdMplsGroupLdpRetryTimesNoroute
usdMplsGroupLdpRetryTimesNoroute.description: Use this object to configure the number of retries for LDP to setup LSP after a failure due to no available route.

usdMplsGroupLdpRetryIntervalNoroute.name: usdMplsGroupLdpRetryIntervalNoroute
usdMplsGroupLdpRetryIntervalNoroute.description: Use this object to configure the time interval between two successive LSP setup retries by LDP after a failure due to no available route.

usdMplsGroupLdpRetryTimes.name: usdMplsGroupLdpRetryTimes
usdMplsGroupLdpRetryTimes.description: Use this object to configure LSP setup retries by LDP after a failure other than one due to no available route.

usdMplsGroupLdpRetryInterval.name: usdMplsGroupLdpRetryInterval
usdMplsGroupLdpRetryInterval.description: Use this object to configure time interval between two LSP setup retries by LDP after a failure other than one due to no available route.

usdMplsGroupLdpSessionRetries.name: usdMplsGroupLdpSessionRetries
usdMplsGroupLdpSessionRetries.description: Use this object to configure the number of LDP session retries.

usdMplsGroupLdpSessionRetryTimer.name: usdMplsGroupLdpSessionRetryTimer
usdMplsGroupLdpSessionRetryTimer.description: Use this object to configure the time interval between two LDP session retries.

usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenIpProfileName.name: usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenIpProfileName
usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenIpProfileName.description: Usually IP interfaces are stacked on top of the MPLS tunnels. The profiled tunnels are associated with IP interfaces with profile of IP interfaces. This object configures the name for the IP profile.

usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpInt.name: usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpIntf
usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpInt.description: This object allows enabling/disabling of IP interfaces created over egress LSPs setup by topology driven LSP setup configurations.

usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpIn.name: usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpIntf
usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpIn.description: This object allows enabling/disabling of IP interfaces created over ingress LSPs setup by topology driven LSP setup configurations.

usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpInt.name: usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpIntfHostOnly
usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpInt.description: This object allows enabling/disabling of IP interfaces created over egress LSPs to host only IP addresses setup by topology driven LSP setup configurations.

usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpIn.name: usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpIntfHostOnly
usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpIn.description: This object allows enabling/disabling of IP interfaces created over ingress LSPs to host only IP addresses setup by topology driven LSP setup configurations.

usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpInt.name: usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpIntfPolicyListType
usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpInt.description: There are two types of policy list type defined for the locally defined labels advertisement to neighbors; viz. accessList and prefixList. This object allows configuration of the egress side of LSR for topology driven LSPs. Set the list type and list name cuncurrently.

usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpIn.name: usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpIntfPolicyListType
usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpIn.description: There are two types of policy list type defined for the locally defined labels advertisement to neighbors; viz. accessList and prefixList. This object allows configuration of the ingress side of LSR for topology driven LSPs. Set the list type and list name cuncurrently.

usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpInt.name: usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpIntfPolicyList
usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpEgressIpInt.description: This object used to configure egress list name of topology driven LSPs over IP interfaces. For successful configurations the egress list name must be set cunncurently with egress list type. Set the list type and list name cuncurrently.

usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpIn.name: usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpIntfPolicyList
usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdpIngressIpIn.description: This object used to configure ingress list name of topology driven LSPs over IP interfaces. For successful configurations ingress listname set cunncurently with ingress list type. Set the list type and list name cuncurrently.

usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdp.name: usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdp
usdMplsGroupTopologyDrivenLdp.description: LDP is used for label distributions control for setting up the LSPs. Topology driven LSPs also setup using LDP label distribution control. This object allows to enable/disable LDP admin state used for topology driven LSPs setup.

usdMplsGroupLspLabelDistCtrlMode.name: usdMplsGroupLspLabelDistCtrlMode
usdMplsGroupLspLabelDistCtrlMode.description: Some FECs correspond to address prefixes which are distributed via a dynamic routing algorithm. The setup of the LSPs for these FECs can be done in one of two ways: Independent LSP Control or Ordered LSP Control. This object displays the LSP lable distribution control mode.

usdMplsGroupLdpAdvHostOnly.name: usdMplsGroupLdpAdvHostOnly
usdMplsGroupLdpAdvHostOnly.description: This object allows to enable/disable LDP label advertisement mode for host only LSPs.

usdMplsGroupLsrState.name: usdMplsGroupLsrState
usdMplsGroupLsrState.description: This object value displays the status of MPLS enabled LSR such as state is up or down etc.

usdMplsGroupReopNow.name: usdMplsGroupReopNow
usdMplsGroupReopNow.description: All LSPs setup in MPLS domain are reoptimized for better LSPs as and when available. Setting this object forces an immediate check for better paths for the existing LSPs.

usdMplsGroupTargetedHelloSendTable.name: usdMplsGroupTargetedHelloSendTable
usdMplsGroupTargetedHelloSendTable.description: This table contains list of send side IP addresses for LDP targeted hello messages.

usdMplsGroupTargetedHelloSendEntry.name: usdMplsGroupTargetedHelloSendEntry
usdMplsGroupTargetedHelloSendEntry.description: Each entry represents send IP address for targeted hello message.

usdMplsGroupTargetedHelloSendAddress.name: usdMplsGroupTargetedHelloSendAddress
usdMplsGroupTargetedHelloSendAddress.description: Configure the send side address for targeted hello messages.

usdMplsGroupLdpTargetedHelloSendMode.name: usdMplsGroupLdpTargetedHelloSendMode
usdMplsGroupLdpTargetedHelloSendMode.description: Select mode to add/delete to the list of IP addresses for targeted hello messages.

usdMplsGroupTargetedHelloReceiveTable.name: usdMplsGroupTargetedHelloReceiveTable
usdMplsGroupTargetedHelloReceiveTable.description: This table contains list of receive side IP addresses for LDP targeted hello messages.

usdMplsGroupTargetedHelloReceiveEntry.name: usdMplsGroupTargetedHelloReceiveEntry
usdMplsGroupTargetedHelloReceiveEntry.description: Each entry represents receive IP address for targeted hello message.

usdMplsGroupTargetedHelloReceiveAddress.name: usdMplsGroupTargetedHelloReceiveAddress
usdMplsGroupTargetedHelloReceiveAddress.description: Configure the receive side address for targeted hello messages.

usdMplsGroupLdpTargetedHelloReceiveMode.name: usdMplsGroupLdpTargetedHelloReceiveMode
usdMplsGroupLdpTargetedHelloReceiveMode.description: Select mode to add/delete to the list of IP addresses for targeted hello messages.

usdMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverRouteListTable.name: usdMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverRouteListTable
usdMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverRouteListTable.description: Table is a list of LDP label advertisement entries.

usdMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverRouteListEntry.name: usdMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverRouteListEntry
usdMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverRouteListEntry.description: Each entry represents access list pairs for the LDP peers label advertisement.

usdMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverRouteListName.name: usdMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverRouteListName
usdMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverRouteListName.description: This LDP label advertisement route list name for which this entry contains information.

usdMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverNbrListName.name: usdMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverNbrListName
usdMplsGroupLdpLabelAdverNbrListName.description: The LDP label advertisement neighbor route list name for which this entry contains information.

usdMplsGroupLabelAdverListMode.name: usdMplsGroupLabelAdverListMode
usdMplsGroupLabelAdverListMode.description: This object selects the mode of addition/deletion to the list.

usdMplsGroupLdpProfileTable.name: usdMplsGroupLdpProfileTable
usdMplsGroupLdpProfileTable.description: Table is a list of LDP Profile entries.

usdMplsGroupLdpProfileEntry.name: usdMplsGroupLdpProfileEntry
usdMplsGroupLdpProfileEntry.description: Each entry represents one LDP profile settings.

usdMplsGroupLdpProfileName.name: usdMplsGroupLdpProfileName
usdMplsGroupLdpProfileName.description: LDP profile name identifies unique entry in the table.

usdMplsGroupLdpProfileHelloHoldTime.name: usdMplsGroupLdpProfileHelloHoldTime
usdMplsGroupLdpProfileHelloHoldTime.description: Configure the LDP peers hello hold time period.

usdMplsGroupLdpProfileCrLdpAdminState.name: usdMplsGroupLdpProfileCrLdpAdminState
usdMplsGroupLdpProfileCrLdpAdminState.description: Enable or disable the constraint-based routing label distribution protocol (CR-LDP) admin state.

usdMplsGroupLdpProfileRowStatus.name: usdMplsGroupLdpProfileRowStatus
usdMplsGroupLdpProfileRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: usdMplsGroupLdpProfileCrLdpAdminState usdMplsGroupLdpProfileRowStatus

usdMplsGroupRsvpProfileTable.name: usdMplsGroupRsvpProfileTable
usdMplsGroupRsvpProfileTable.description: Table is a list of LDP Profile entries.

usdMplsGroupRsvpProfileEntry.name: usdMplsGroupRsvpProfileEntry
usdMplsGroupRsvpProfileEntry.description: Each entry represents one LDP profile settings.

usdMplsGroupRsvpProfileName.name: usdMplsGroupRsvpProfileName
usdMplsGroupRsvpProfileName.description: The RSVP profile name identifies unique entry in the table.

usdMplsGroupRsvpProfileRefreshPeriod.name: usdMplsGroupRsvpProfileRefreshPeriod
usdMplsGroupRsvpProfileRefreshPeriod.description: Configure the time out period between the generation of two refresh messages.

usdMplsGroupRsvpProfileCleanupTimeoutFac.name: usdMplsGroupRsvpProfileCleanupTimeoutFactor
usdMplsGroupRsvpProfileCleanupTimeoutFac.description: Confgure the number of refresh messages can be lost before PATH or RESV state is ended.

usdMplsGroupRsvpProfileRowStatus.name: usdMplsGroupRsvpProfileRowStatus
usdMplsGroupRsvpProfileRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry object MUST be explicitly configured: usdMplsGroupRsvpProfileRowStatus

usdMplsIfMajorNextIfIndex.name: usdMplsIfMajorNextIfIndex
usdMplsIfMajorNextIfIndex.description: Coordinate ifIndex value allocation for entries in the usdMplsIfMajorTable. A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

usdMplsIfMajorTable.name: usdMplsIfMajorTable
usdMplsIfMajorTable.description: This table contains entries for MPLS Major interfaces present in the system.

usdMplsIfMajorEntry.name: usdMplsIfMajorEntry
usdMplsIfMajorEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an MPLS Major interface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries to be created/deleted in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable.

usdMplsIfMajorIndex.name: usdMplsIfMajorIndex
usdMplsIfMajorIndex.description: The ifIndex of the MPLS Major interface. When creating entries in this table, suitable values for this object are determined by reading usdMplsIfMajorNextIfIndex.

usdMplsIfMajorRowStatus.name: usdMplsIfMajorRowStatus
usdMplsIfMajorRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: usdMplsIfMajorRowStatus usdMplsIfMajorLowerIfIndex In addition, when creating an entry the following conditions must hold: A value for usdMplsIfMajorIndex must have been determined previously, by reading usdMplsIfMajorNextIfIndex. A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable is created/ destroyed as a result of creating/destroying an entry in this table.

usdMplsIfMajorLowerIfIndex.name: usdMplsIfMajorLowerIfIndex
usdMplsIfMajorLowerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an interface over which this MPLS Major interface to be layered. A value of zero indicates no layering. An implementation may choose to require that a nonzero value be configured at entry creation.

usdMplsIfMajorAdminStatus.name: usdMplsIfMajorAdminStatus
usdMplsIfMajorAdminStatus.description: Use this object to create MPLS major interface stacked over any link layer interface. Lower layer(index) over which major stacks has to be specified for successful creation of the major interface.

usdMplsIfMajorLdpAdminStatus.name: usdMplsIfMajorLdpAdminStatus
usdMplsIfMajorLdpAdminStatus.description: This object enables/disables LDP admin status on the MPLS interface.

usdMplsIfMajorLdpProfileName.name: usdMplsIfMajorLdpProfileName
usdMplsIfMajorLdpProfileName.description: All the LDP settings on the MPLS interface be will associated with the profile. This object allows to associate those configured settings to interface by using the LDP profile name.

usdMplsIfMajorLdpVpiStart.name: usdMplsIfMajorLdpVpiStart
usdMplsIfMajorLdpVpiStart.description: This object is defined to support configurations of interface label space. This configures the start range of the LDP VPI. For successful configuration of interface label space LDP VPI ranges, set this object with the stop range cunncurrently.

usdMplsIfMajorLdpVpiStop.name: usdMplsIfMajorLdpVpiStop
usdMplsIfMajorLdpVpiStop.description: This object is defined to support configurations of interface label space. This configures the stop range of the LDP VPI. For successful configuration of interface label space LDP VPI ranges, set this object with the start range cunncurrently.

usdMplsIfMajorLdpVciStart.name: usdMplsIfMajorLdpVciStart
usdMplsIfMajorLdpVciStart.description: This object is defined to support configurations of interface label space. This configures the start range of the LDP VCI. For successful configuration of interface label space LDP VCI ranges, set this object with the stop range cunncurrently.

usdMplsIfMajorLdpVciStop.name: usdMplsIfMajorLdpVciStop
usdMplsIfMajorLdpVciStop.description: This object is defined to support configurations of interface label space. This configures the stop range of the LDP VCI. For successful configuration of interface label space LDP VCI ranges, set this object with the start range cunncurrently.

usdMplsIfMajorRsvpAdminStatus.name: usdMplsIfMajorRsvpAdminStatus
usdMplsIfMajorRsvpAdminStatus.description: This object configures RSVP admin status for MPLS interface.

usdMplsIfMajorRsvpProfileName.name: usdMplsIfMajorRsvpProfileName
usdMplsIfMajorRsvpProfileName.description: All the RSVP settings on the MPLS interface be will associated with the profile. This object allows to associate those configured settings to interface by using the RSVP profile name.

usdMplsIfMajorRsvpVpiStart.name: usdMplsIfMajorRsvpVpiStart
usdMplsIfMajorRsvpVpiStart.description: This object is defined to support configurations of interface label space. This configures the start range of the RSVP VPI. For successful configuration of interface label space RSVP VPI ranges, set this object with the stop range cunncurrently.

usdMplsIfMajorRsvpVpiStop.name: usdMplsIfMajorRsvpVpiStop
usdMplsIfMajorRsvpVpiStop.description: This object is defined to support configurations of interface label space. This configures the stop range of the RSVP VPI. For successful configuration of interface label space RSVP VPI ranges, set this object with the start range cunncurrently.

usdMplsIfMajorRsvpVciStart.name: usdMplsIfMajorRsvpVciStart
usdMplsIfMajorRsvpVciStart.description: This object is defined to support configurations of interface label space. This configures the start range of the RSVP VCI. For successful configuration of interface label space RSVP VCI ranges, set this object with the stop range cunncurrently.

usdMplsIfMajorRsvpVciStop.name: usdMplsIfMajorRsvpVciStop
usdMplsIfMajorRsvpVciStop.description: This object is defined to support configurations of interface label space. This configures the stop range of the RSVP VCI. For successful configuration of interface label space RSVP VCI ranges, set this object with the start range cunncurrently.

usdMplsIfMajorLabelSpaceType.name: usdMplsIfMajorLabelSpaceType
usdMplsIfMajorLabelSpaceType.description: Displays the label space type for the MPLS interface.

usdMplsIfMajorOpState.name: usdMplsIfMajorOpState
usdMplsIfMajorOpState.description: This object displays MPLS major interface operation state.

usdMplsIfMajorCrLdpAdminState.name: usdMplsIfMajorCrLdpAdminState
usdMplsIfMajorCrLdpAdminState.description: This object displays the admin state of CR-LDP.

usdMplsIfMinorNextIfIndex.name: usdMplsIfMinorNextIfIndex
usdMplsIfMinorNextIfIndex.description: Coordinates ifIndex value allocation for entries in the usdMplsIfMinorTable. A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

usdMplsIfMinorTable.name: usdMplsIfMinorTable
usdMplsIfMinorTable.description: This table contains entries for MPLS Minor interfaces present in the system.

usdMplsIfMinorEntry.name: usdMplsIfMinorEntry
usdMplsIfMinorEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an MPLS Minor interface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries for be created/deleted in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable.

usdMplsIfMinorIndex.name: usdMplsIfMinorIndex
usdMplsIfMinorIndex.description: The ifIndex of the MPLS Minor interface. When creating entries in this table, suitable values for this object are determined by reading usdMplsMinorNextIfIndex.

usdMplsIfMinorRowStatus.name: usdMplsIfMinorRowStatus
usdMplsIfMinorRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: usdMplsIfMinorRowStatus usdMplsIfMinorTunnelName In addition, when creating an entry the following conditions must hold: A value for usdMplsIfMinorIndex must have been determined previously, by reading usdMplsMinorNextIfIndex. A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable is created/ destroyed as a result of creating/destroying an entry in this table.

usdMplsIfMinorLowerIfIndex.name: usdMplsIfMinorLowerIfIndex
usdMplsIfMinorLowerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an interface over which this MPLS Minor interface is to be layered. A value of zero indicates no layering. As minor interface can be created without stacking on major interface, as and when it stacks on major interface by signalling protocol, it's value can be read.

usdMplsIfMinorAdminStatus.name: usdMplsIfMinorAdminStatus
usdMplsIfMinorAdminStatus.description: With this object minor interface admin status can be enabled/disabled.

usdMplsIfMinorEndpointAddress.name: usdMplsIfMinorEndpointAddress
usdMplsIfMinorEndpointAddress.description: This object configures the IP address of the tunnel destination. This object can be set along with the usdMplsIfMinorEndpointDstMask to configure the tunnel destination mask, but it is optional.

usdMplsIfMinorEndpointDstMask.name: usdMplsIfMinorEndpointDstMask
usdMplsIfMinorEndpointDstMask.description: This object configures the tunnel destination mask. It can be set along with the usdMplsIfMinorEndpointAddress.

usdMplsIfMinorTunnelMetricMode.name: usdMplsIfMinorTunnelMetricMode
usdMplsIfMinorTunnelMetricMode.description: Select the relative or absolute mode to configure the absolute or relative tunnel metric. To set the tunnel to relative metric, usdMplsIfMinorRelativeTunnelMetric has to be set along with this object option as relative. To set the tunnel to absolute metric, usdMplsIfMinorAbsoluteTunnelMetric has to be set along with this object option as absolute.

usdMplsIfMinorAbsoluteTunnelMetric.name: usdMplsIfMinorAbsoluteTunnelMetric
usdMplsIfMinorAbsoluteTunnelMetric.description: This object allows configuration of absolute metric values. Refer to usdMplsIfMinorTunnelMetricMode for how set it.

usdMplsIfMinorRelativeTunnelMetric.name: usdMplsIfMinorRelativeTunnelMetric
usdMplsIfMinorRelativeTunnelMetric.description: This object allows configuration of relative metric values. Refer to usdMplsIfMinorTunnelMetricMode for how set it.

usdMplsIfMinorLabelDistProto.name: usdMplsIfMinorLabelDistProto
usdMplsIfMinorLabelDistProto.description: This object allows to select label distribution protocol. Label distribution protocols are used by two LSRs to negotiate label to FEC binding to set up tunnels.

usdMplsIfMinorAnnounceToOspf.name: usdMplsIfMinorAnnounceToOspf
